
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `hp-scan` baraye estefade az scanner-e printer-haye HP az tarighe khat-e farman (terminal) be kar miravad. Ba in dastoor mitoonid aks ha ya asnad ro scan konid va save konid.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `hp-scan -g` --> 🖼️ Baz kardane GUI (Graphical User Interface) baraye ayar-haye bishtar
    🔹 `hp-scan -o <filename>` --> 💾 Save kardane scan ba name file-e moshakhas
    🔹 `hp-scan --mode <color|grayscale|lineart>` --> 🌈 Tarz-e scan ro moshakhas mikone (rangi, khakestari, siyah-o-sefid)
    🔹 `hp-scan --resolution <dpi>` --> 🎯 Deghat-e scan ro moshakhas mikone (dots per inch)

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ hp-scan

    🔹 Scan kardan ba ayar-haye pishfarz va save kardan be name pishfarz.

    $ hp-scan -o document.pdf

    🔹 Scan kardan va save kardan be name "document.pdf".

    $ hp-scan --mode grayscale --resolution 300 -o gray_doc.jpg

    🔹 Scan kardan be soorat khakestari ba deghat 300 dpi va save kardan be name "gray_doc.jpg".

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ hp-scan -g

    🔹 Baz kardane panjare-ye GUI baraye scan kardan. Shoma mitoonid settings ro tagheer bedid va aks ro pish az save kardan bebinid.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `hp-scan` command is used to operate the scanner function of HP printers through the command line (terminal). It allows you to scan images or documents and save them.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `hp-scan -g` --> 🖼️ Opens the GUI (Graphical User Interface) for more settings
    🔹 `hp-scan -o <filename>` --> 💾 Saves the scan with the specified filename
    🔹 `hp-scan --mode <color|grayscale|lineart>` --> 🌈 Specifies the scan mode (color, grayscale, black and white)
    🔹 `hp-scan --resolution <dpi>` --> 🎯 Specifies the scan resolution (dots per inch)

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ hp-scan

    🔹 Scan with default settings and save with the default filename.

    $ hp-scan -o document.pdf

    🔹 Scan and save as "document.pdf".

    $ hp-scan --mode grayscale --resolution 300 -o gray_doc.jpg

    🔹 Scan in grayscale at 300 dpi resolution and save as "gray_doc.jpg".

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ hp-scan -g

    🔹 Opens the GUI window for scanning. You can change settings and preview the image before saving.
